headline: Billionaires Are Selling Nvidia Stock and Buying a Stock-Split AI Stock Up 530% in 5 Years
summary: A few hedge fund billionaires during the first quarter sold Nvidia and bought Arista Networks, a stock that recently split and has returned 530% in the last five years.  Nvidia has struggled with headwinds related to DeepSeek and chip export controls, but the company is still ideally positioned to monetize demand for AI infrastructure.  Arista is the market leader in high-speed Ethernet switches, devices that play a critical role in supporting artificial intelligence applications in data centers.
